  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail Password?",
  "response": "To reset your Gmail password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Gmail sign-in page**: Open your web browser and navigate to the Gmail sign-in page at [gmail.com](https://www.gmail.com).\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgot password?\"**: After you enter your email address, click on the \"Next\" button. When prompted to enter your password, click on \"Forgot password?\"\n\n3. **Verify your identity**: You will be asked to verify your identity. Google may offer several methods, such as sending a verification code to your recovery email address or SMS to your registered phone number. Choose your preferred recovery method and follow the prompts.\n\n4. **Enter the verification code**: If you receive a code, enter it in the designated field and click \"Next.\"\n\n5. **Create a new password**: Once you successfully verify your identity, you will be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it is strong and secure.\n\n6. **Save your new password**: After entering the new password, click \"Next\" to save it. You should now be able to log in to your Gmail account with the new password.\n\n7. **Update your password manager**: If you use a password manager, remember to update it with your new password.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can follow the on-screen instructions for further assistance.",
